                        <h1>Global Media Awards</h1>                                  
                        <P><A href="http://www.globalmediaawards.org/" target=_blank></A><IMG src="/print/images/content/gma-logo2.jpg" align=right border=0>The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) and the National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences (NATAS)&nbsp;are partnering to&nbsp;launch a new <A href="http://www.globalmediaawards.org/" target=_blank><STRONG>Global Media Awards program</STRONG></A> focused on technology and content programming at the 2009 CES. <BR><BR>Peter O. Price, President and CEO of NATAS, applauded the joint initiative, noting, "We anticipate wide participation and attendance at the ceremony, which will invite entries from a broad spectrum of creators, producers, and distributors of content and technologies."<BR><BR>A call for entries for the Global Media Awards and details about the ceremony on January 8, 2009, will be released later this month. For information about the Global Media Awards, contact Paul Pillitteri at <A href="mailto:ppillitteri@natasonline.com" target=blank>ppillitteri@natasonline.com</A>&nbsp;or visit <A href="http://globalmediaawards.org/" target=_blank><FONT face=Arial size=2>http://globalmediaawards.org/</FONT></A>.<BR></P>
